Company Short Description:
Atlanta's Sheley, Hall & Williams is a boutique real estate law firm offering specialized expertise and representation to clients in all areas of commercial real estate, including leasing, development, acquisitions, dispositions, joint ventures and real estate finance.

Sheley, Hall & Williams represents institutional portfolio owners, private equity real estate funds, development companies, corporate owners and real estate investors, including opportunistic buyers, throughout the United States.  The firm was founded as, and remains, a real estate "boutique" specializing in the following areas:

*  leasing of office, industrial and retail space, primarily representing owners;
*  development of office, industrial, hotel, multifamily and mixed-use retail projects;
*  private equity investment, including joint venture agreements for acquisition 
   and development projects;
*  negotiation of hotel management agreements;
*  acquisition and disposition of existing office, industrial, multi-family, hotel 
   and mixed-use retail projects;
*  local counsel advice with respect to acquisition and financing transactions, including 
   Georgia enforceability opinions; and
*  general real estate legal services for corporate owners of real property, including asset 
   management, leasing and ownership.

At Sheley, Hall & Williams, we combine the expertise of highly experienced lawyers and other legal professionals with the most up-to-date technology to ensure a timely, effective and efficient work product. Our focus is on understanding the business objectives of our clients and helping them to achieve their goals as expeditiously and cost-effectively as possible.

